gomodel:SYNGO_2275  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Over expression of EGFP-p65 allowed the investigation of the protein redistribution from the dendritic brunch to the nucleus using a FRAP approach.\nFollowing photobleaching of a dendritic segment, authors observed fluorescence recovery which was unidirectional and triggered only by NMDA application. Accordingly, photobleaching of the somatic region shows a significant recovery after NMDA application, different from the recovery observed under basal conditions.. Experimental description: Dissociated primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from postnatal P1 mice.\n\nThere is no information whatsoever about the origin of the p65 sequence they used for their clones.\n\n24/01/2018 Pim\n- Authors contacted for species information (dd 24/01/2018\n mkm@jhmi.edu). Aswer via phone: \"human\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2275" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

